<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 2:32PM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...A THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT EAST CENTRAL IREDELL AND NORTHWESTERN
ROWAN COUNTIES UNTIL 300 PM EDT...
At 232 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a thunderstorm 4 miles east
of Statesville, moving northeast at 10 mph.
Locations to be impacted include...
Statesville, Cleveland, Cool Springs and Turnersburg.
Very heavy rainfall rates up to 2 inches per hour will be possible in
these areas.</description>
<instruction>The combination of gusty winds and saturated soil conditions will
cause scattered trees and power lines to fall. Seek shelter inside an
interior room.</instruction>
